<sect> colors
<p>
<descrip>
<tag> Synopsis </tag> Sets the terminal foreground and background color. 
	Resets the terminal color scheme to default values.
<tag> Syntax </tag>
             <p> colors ( <em>fg</em>, <em>bg</em> )
             <p> colors ( )

<tag> Arguments </tag>

	<descrip>
	<tag> fg / bg </tag>
		name of the color, "default", "red", "green", "yellow" or "brown",
		"blue", "magenta", "cyan", "grey" or "white".				
	<tag> none </tag>
		resets the terminal to its default values.
	</descrip>		

	colors uses termcap library.
	
	<tag>See Also</tag> clrscr, mvcrsr, clrpos.

</descrip>
